Response ID: resp_2382
Response Text: With both the school for the blind and deaf here in Austin, perhaps ACME can have a program to help better integrate these communities into the arts - both as participants and audience members. They're still pretty siloed and I think that's unfortunate from artistic and access points of view. I have both CODA and blind friends, and not many organizations think about creating accessible programs or information for them or their families. Also, hiring ASL interpretation is very expensive for small arts organizations.

It could be cool for ACME to think about how they can facilitate these kinds of connections and supports better. Can ACME take on some of the logistical responsibility for helping forge/create this access?

